name: 5'HA-hAAVS1-new
comment: Homology arm for targeting of hAVVS1 locus. Genomic position 19:55627206-55628020

name: 5'-ITR-PB
comment: transposon-specific inverted terminal repeat sequences (ITRs) recognized by PiggyBac transposase

name: Chimeric-5'LTR
comment: Chimeric 5'LTR for lentiviral vectors :It contains an RSV promoter, a truncated 5'LTR and other lentiviral elements such as Phi element, cPPT/CTS and RRE. Note: it contains an internal BsaI site that has not been removed to not alter the original sequence

name: Minimal_UCOE
comment: Minimal ubiquitous chromatin opening element. Position 2. Minimal region of a methylation-free CpG island from the human HNRPA2B1-CBX3 housekeeping genes (A2UCOE) that effectively prevents transgene silencing and variegation in cell lines, multipotent and pluripotent stem cells, and their differentiated progeny. doi: 10.1093/nar/gkv019

name: Insulator_FB
comment: FII/BEAD-A (FB) element. (STEMCELLS2008;26:3257–3266 ). FII/BEAD-A (FB) contains the minimal enhancer-blocking components of the chicken b-globin 5'HS4 insulator and a homologous region from the human T-cell receptor  BEAD-1 insulator

name: CAGp
comment: strong synthetic promoter used to drive high levels of gene expression in mammalian expression vectors. constructed in the lab of Dr Jun-ichi Miyazaki [3][4] from the following sequences: (C) the cytomegalovirus (CMV) early enhancer element + (A) the promoter, the first exon and the first intron of chicken beta-actin gene + (G) the splice acceptor of the rabbit beta-globin gene.

name: CMVp_Tet
comment: Tetracycline repressible CMV promoter. CMV promoter with downstream operator sequences for TetRepressor.

name: EF1ap
comment: strong constitutive promoter derived from  endogenous promoter of human elongation factor EF-1α . EF-1 alpha is often useful in conditions where other promoters (such as CMV) have diminished activity or have been silenced (as in embryonic stem cells)

name: TRE3Gp
comment: 3rd-generation Tet-responsive promoter that can be activated by binding of Tet-On® 3G

name: EF-1ap_core
comment: EF-1a core promoter: Minimal sequence required for EF1a promoter. This promoter is an endogenous promoter for Elongation Factor 1 and therefore is less subject to silencing. EF-1α promoter directs more stable long-term gene expression than the for instance CMV promoter.

name: HSV_TKp
comment: HSV_TK promoter (Human Tymidine Kinase gene promoter). it is a relatively weak promoter. Note: mutation introduced to remove a BsaI site (388 G>C). This new version has not been tested

name: LacI -operator
comment: DNA recognition site for Lac-repressor protein

name: Kt-L7Ae - Weiss
comment: L7Ae:K-turn system. K-t = K-turn, recognition sequence for RNA-binding protein L7Ae  . L7Ae then binds the K-turn motifs in the 5′ UTR of RNA and block the ribosome binding to the mRNA.  doi:10.1038/nbt.3301. Binding protein L7Ae is clone YCe2772

name: K1-K1 -L7Ae
comment: L7Ae:K-turn system. K = K-turn, recognition sequence for RNA-binding protein L7Ae  . L7Ae then binds the K-turn motifs in the 5′ UTR of RNA and block the ribosome binding to the mRNA.   - original article?? - binding protein L2A7 from clone YCe2032

name: Kt-Kt -L7Ae-Weiss
comment: L7Ae:K-turn system. K-t = K-turn, recognition sequence for RNA-binding protein L7Ae  . L7Ae then binds the K-turn motifs in the 5′ UTR of RNA and block the ribosome binding to the mRNA.  doi:10.1038/nbt.3301  Binding protein L7Ae is clone YCe2772

name: ATG-BoxC (L7Ae)
comment: BoxC recognized by RNA binding protein L7Ae.  L7Ae then binds theBoxC motif placed after the ATG and block translation of the CDS. dOI: 10.1038/nCHeMBIO.273

name: Tet-Aptazyme
comment: Tetracycline-inducible  aptazyme. It is a ribozyme that once placed in the 3'UTR causes RNA self-cleavage. The mRNA loses the polyA and is degraded. The result is a posttranscriptional downregulation of gene expression.  The ribozyme is fused with an aptamer that recognizes tetracycline. In presence of Tet the aptazyme is inactivated and the mRNA is not degraded.  dx.doi.org/10.1021/sb500270h | ACS Synth. Biol. 2015, 4, 526−534
